The paper deals with kernel methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and fall under the category of statistical learning theory. The focus of the paper is on developing a novel optimal design for kernel expansion, which suggests that it could fall under the category of optimization and control (cs.OC). However, the paper primarily discusses the theoretical analysis of the proposed method and its performance on benchmark datasets, indicating that it could also belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Among these, cs.LG is the most likely category as it is directly related to the paper's topic and methodology.
